# Memory Index

## Memory Governance
Before any persistent memory read, write, compress, or archive action, apply the `memory-rule` plugin skill.

Use the `memory-rule` plugin skill when:
- updating `MEMORY.md`
- writing to `notes/`
- promoting task facts into durable memory
- compressing or archiving completed work
- resolving conflicting preferences, rules, or corrections

## Sync Trigger
If durable local memory or managed workspace config changes need cross-device retention, use the `sync-request` plugin skill to create a sync request in `~/sync-queue/pending/` for Adam.
Do not run sync directly from this agent.

## Key Knowledge
- `notes/user-preferences.md` — collaboration preferences and constraints
- `notes/agent-workflow.md` — agent-local workflow and operational defaults
- `notes/findings.md` — findings, corrections, and meta-knowledge

